# Transformations and actions — RDD edition

## Transformations — lazy, build the recipe

- `map(f)` — one in, one out
- `flatMap(f)` — one in, zero-or-more out, then flatten
- `filter(f)` — keep where `f` is truthy
- `distinct()` — drop duplicates *(shuffle)*
- `union(rdd2)` — concatenate
- `repartition(n)` / `coalesce(n)` — change partition count

## Actions — trigger execution

- `count()` · `take(n)` / `first()`
- `collect()` — all elements to the driver *(careful on big data)*
- `reduce(f)` — pairwise aggregate
- `saveAsTextFile(path)` — one file per partition

**Nothing runs until an action fires.**
